    "(2) Data licenses to some extent reflect the openness and accessibility of datasets.",
    "For instruction fine-tuning datasets, the Apache-2.0 license is the most commonly used, covering 43 datasets, followed by the GPL-3.0 license and the MIT license.",
    "This reflects the developers' inclination towards open and shared data.",
    "(3) The majority of instruction fine-tuning datasets are concentrated in the range of 10K to 1M, totaling 63 datasets.",
    "This indicates that, in practical applications, datasets of this scale are sufficient to meet the demand."
